txt.en: The crate is filled with shattered pieces of pottery. The pieces indicate that several pots are missing. The quality of the smashed ones is very high, and the pattern is foreign to Dunland. If any remain they would bring a good price at auction.
After removing the smashed pieces, the pots easily fit within the crate. They may bounce a little during the ride, but they should make it intact.
The paint and patterns on the pottery are striking in their beauty; however, they are clearly not Dunlending in design.
The crate is filled with shattered pieces of pottery. The pieces indicate that several pots are missing.
The pottery missing from the crate must have been taken into the hills to the east by the Dragon-clan raiders.\n\nYou should recover the missing pottery.
Return the pots to the crate
The crate to safely transport the remaining pots is at Andras' cart on the northern road of Starkmoor.\n\nThe pots should be returned to the crate from which they were stolen.
